trans-unit.source: O Allah, separate me from my sins as You have separated the East from the West. O Allah, cleanse me of my transgressions as the white garment is cleansed of stains. O Allah, wash away my sins with ice and water and frost.
trans-unit.target: የ በምዕራብ እስከ ምሥራቅ ተለያዩ እንደ የኾንክ አላህ ሆይ: ኃጢአት ከእኔ ይለያቸዋል.

trans-unit.source: Glory is to You, O Allah, and praise, Blessed is Your Name and Exalted is Your Majesty, There is none worthy of worship but You.
trans-unit.target: ክብር አንተ ነው: አምልኮ ግን አንተ ሊሆን አይገባውም; አስተዋይም የለም; ብፁዓን ሆይ አላህ, እና ውዳሴ, የእርስዎ ስም ነው አሸናፊ ግርማዊነትዎ ነው.

trans-unit.source: I turn my face towards the One Who created the heavens and the earth, as a true believer. I am not of those who associate partners with Allah. Verily, my prayer and my devotion, my living and my death, are for Allah, Lord of the worlds, He has no partners. Thus I have been commanded and I am among those who have submitted. O Allah, You are the King, there is none worthy of worship but You. You are my Lord and I am Your slave. I have wronged my own soul and confess my sin. Forgive all of my sins, surely none forgives sins but You. Guide me to the perfection of my character, for none guides to its perfection but You. Protect me from the evils of my character, for none may protect me from its evils but You. I am here at Your service. All goodness is in Your Hands, and evil is not attributed to You. I am (created) by You, and I am (returning) to You. You are Most Blessed, Most Exalted. I seek Your forgiveness and repent to You.
trans-unit.target: እኔ እውነተኛ አማኝ እንደሆነች, ሰማያትንና ምድርን የፈጠረ ማን እንደ አንዱ አቅጣጫ ፊቴን ያብሩ.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, Lord of Jibra'il, Mika'il and Israfil. Maker of the heavens and the earth. Knower of the unseen and the seen. You judge between Your slaves regarding that in which they differ. Guide me to the truth regarding that in which there is difference, by Your Leave. Surely, You guide whomever you please to the straight path.
trans-unit.target: የኾንክ አላህ Jibra'il, Mika'il እና ኢስራፊል ጌታ.

trans-unit.source: Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Glory is to Allah, at the break of day and at its end. (3x). I seek refuge in Allah from Satan, From his breath and from his voice and from his whisper.

O Allah, praise is to You. You are the light of the heavens and the earth and all that they contain. Praise is to You, You are the Sustainer of the heavens and the earth and all they contain. (Praise is to You, You are the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all they contain.) (Praise is to You, Yours is dominion of the heavens and the earth and all they contain.) (Praise is to You, You are the King of the heavens and the earth.) (And praise is to you.) (You are the truth, Your Promise is true, Your Word is true, Your audience is true, Paradise is true, Hell is true, the Prophets are true, and Muhammad (peace and blessings be upon him) is true, and the Hour of Judgement is true.) (O Allah, to You I have submitted, and upon You I depend. I have believed in You and to You I turn in repentence. For Your sake I dispute and by Your standard I judge. Forgive me what I have sent before me and what I have let behind me, what I have concealed and what I have declared.) (You are the One Who sends forth and You are the One Who delays, there is none who has the right to be worshipped but You.) (You are my God, there is none who has the right to be worshipped but You.)

ሰሜን ምዕራብ ቀስት ጋር የተሰበረ ክበብ

trans-unit.source: {How the Divine Inspiration started to be revealed to Allah's Messenger (SAWS). And the Statement of Allah (ta'ala): "Verily, We have inspired you (O Muhammad (SAWS)) as We inspired Nuh (Noah) and the Prophets after him."}4.163
trans-unit.target: {እንዴት መለኮታዊ ተመስጦ ወደ አላህ መልእክተኛ (በሽረት) ይገለጥ ዘንድ ጀመረ.

trans-unit.source: Virtues of Prayer at Masjid Makkah and Madinah
trans-unit.target: መስጊድ በመካ እና የመዲና ላይ ጸሎት በጎነት

trans-unit.source: Pilgrims Prevented from Completing the Pilgrimmage
Penalty of Hunting while on Pilgrimmage
The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'Islam is based on five principles.'
trans-unit.target: ነቢዩ (በሽረት) ያለው መግለጫ: 'ኢስላም በአምስት መሠረታዊ ሥርዓቶች ላይ የተመሠረተ ነው.'

trans-unit.source: To love the Ansar is a sign of faith.
trans-unit.target: የ Ansar መውደድ እምነት ምልክት ነው.

trans-unit.source: To flee (run away) from Al-Fitan (trials and afflications etc.) is a part of religion.
trans-unit.target: አል-Fitan ከ (መሸሽ) ለመሸሽ (ፈተናዎች እና afflications ወዘተ) ሃይማኖት አንዱ አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'I know Allah (azza wa jal) better than all of you do'.
trans-unit.target: ነቢዩ (በሽረት) ያለው መግለጫ: 'እኔ አላህ (azza ወ jal) አውቃለሁ እናንተ ሁሉ ይልቅ የተሻለ ነገር ማድረግ'.

trans-unit.source: Whoever hates to revert to Kufr.
The grades in superiority of the believers will be according to their good deeds.
trans-unit.target: አማኞች ብልጫ ውስጥ ያሉት ክፍሎች ያላቸውን መልካም እንደ ሥራው መጠን ይሆናል.

trans-unit.source: Al-Haya is a part of faith.
The statement of Allah (azza wa jal): "But if they repent and perform Iqamat-as-Salat [offer Salat (prayers) perfectly] and give Zakat then leave their way free."
trans-unit.target: አላህ (azza ወ jal) ያለው መግለጫ: "ነገር ግን ንስሐ እና Iqamat-እንደ-ሰሊት ማከናወን ከሆነ [ቅናሽ ሰሊት (ጸሎት) ፍጹም] እና ዛካት ​​ከዚያም ነጻ በሆነ መንገድ ትተው ስጡ."

trans-unit.source: Whoever says that faith is action (good deeds).
trans-unit.target: ማንም የእምነት እርምጃ (መልካም ሥራ) ነው ይላል.

trans-unit.source: If one does not embrace Islam truly, but does so by compulsion or for fear of being killed etc.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሰው በእውነት እስልምናን እንዲቀበል, ነገር ግን በግድ ወይም ወዘተ እንዳይገደሉ በመፍራት እንዲህ አያደርግም ከሆነ

trans-unit.source: To greet is a part of Islam.
To be ungrateful to one's husband. And disbelief is of different grades.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ባል ወደ ምስጋና ቢስ ይሆናሉ.

trans-unit.source: Sins are from ignorance and a sinner is not a disbeliever unless he worships others along with Allah (azza wa jal).
trans-unit.target: ኃጢአት ባለማወቅ የመጡ ናቸውና አላህ (azza ወ jal) ጋር በመሆን ሌሎችን በማምለክ በስተቀር ኃጢአተኛ disbeliever አይደለም.

trans-unit.source: The statement of Allah (azza wa jal): {"If two parties (or groups) from among the believers fall to fighting, then make peace between them both."}4.49
trans-unit.target: አላህ (azza ወ jal) ያለው መግለጫ: { "አማኞች መካከል ሁለት ፓርቲዎች (ወይም ቡድኖች) ውጊያ ላይ ይወድቃሉ ከሆነ, ከዚያም በሁለቱም መካከል ሰላም መፍጠር."} 4,49

trans-unit.source: Zulm (wrong) of one kind can be greater or lesser than that of another.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ዓይነት Zulm (ስህተት) ሌላ የሚበልጥ ወይም ዝቅ ሊሆን ይችላል.

trans-unit.source: To establish prayers on the night of Qadr is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: ቃዴር ምሽት ላይ ጸሎት ለማቋቋም እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: Al-Jihad (holy war - fighting in Allah's cause) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: አል-ጅሃድ (ቅዱስ ጦርነት - አላህ ምክንያት ውስጥ ከመጋደል) እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: It is a part of faith to establish the (Nawafil - voluntary) prayers during the nights of Ramadan.
trans-unit.target: የረመዳን ሌሊት ጸሎት - ይህ (በፈቃደኝነት Nawafil) ለማቋቋም እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: To observe Saum [fasts (according to Islamic teachings)] during the month of Ramadan (sincerely and faithfully) hoping for Allah's rewards only, is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: ብቻ የአላህን ሽልማት ለማግኘት ተስፋ የረመዳን (በቅንነት እና በታማኝነት) ወር [(የእስልምና አስተምህሮ መሠረት) ጾም] Saum ለማክበር, የእምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: (What is said) regarding the deeds of faith.
The (offering of) Salat (Prayers) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: ሰሊት (ጸሎቶች) መጽሐፍ (ክፍል መባ) እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: (What is said regarding the superiority of) a person who embraces Islam sincerely.
trans-unit.target: ከልብ ኢስላም አቅፎ ሰው (ያለውን የበላይነት በተመለከተ እንዲህ ምንድን ነው).

trans-unit.source: Ad-Din (good righteous deed - act of worship) loved most by Allah (azza wa jal) is that which is done regularly.
trans-unit.target: (መልካም የጽድቅ ሥራ - አምልኮ ድርጊት) Ad-ዲን አላህ (azza ወ jal) በማድረግ በጣም ይወደው በመደበኛነት የሚከናወን ነው ማለት ነው.

trans-unit.source: To pay Zakat is a part of Islam.
To accompany the funeral processions (up to the place of burial) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: የቀብር ሥርዓት ሰልፎችን (የመቃብር ቦታ ድረስ) ጋር አብሮ ለመሄድ እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: The fear of a believer that his good deeds may be annulled (lost) without his knowledge.
trans-unit.target: በመልካም ሥራዎች እውቀት ያለ (የጠፋ) ሊሻር ይችላል አማኝ ፍርሃት.

trans-unit.source: The asking of (angel) Jibrael (Gabriel) from the Prophet (SAWS) about Belief, Islam, Ihsan (perfection).
trans-unit.target: ማመን ስለ ነቢዩ በሽረት አባባል (አይደለም) ከ (መልአክ) የገብርኤል (ገብርኤል) ዘ ጠይቀን, እስላም, Ihsan (ፍጽምና).

trans-unit.source: A Muslim is the one who avoids harming Muslims with his tongue and hands.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሙስሊም ምላሱን እና እጅ ጋር አይተላለፍ ሙስሊሞች ይጠነቀቃል ሰው ነው.

trans-unit.source: The superiority of that person who leaves all doubtful (unclear) things for the sake of his religion.
trans-unit.target: የእርሱ ሃይማኖት ስል ሁሉን አጠራጣሪ (ግልጽ ያልሆነ) ነገሮችን ትቶ ሰው በዚያ ሰው ብልጫ.

trans-unit.source: To pay Al-Khumus (one-fifth of the war booty to be given in Allah's cause) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: አል-Khumus (ጦርነቱ ብዝበዛ ያስቀሩት ምርኮ አንድ አምስተኛው በአላህ ምክንያት የተሰጠ ዘንድ) ለመክፈል እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: What is said regarding the statement: 'The reward of deeds depends upon the intention.'
trans-unit.target: ምን መግለጫ በተመለከተ እንዲህ ነው: '. ሥራ ምንዳ በማሰብ ላይ የተመካ ነው'

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'Religion is An-Nasiha [(to be sincere and true) to Allah, to His Messenger, to the Muslim rulers, and to all the Muslims.]'
trans-unit.target: ነቢዩ (በሽረት) ያለው መግለጫ: 'ሃይማኖት አንድ-Nasiha ነው [. አላህ, በመልክተኛው, ሙስሊም ገዥዎች ሁሉ ሙስሊሞች (ቅን እና እውነተኛ መሆን)]'

trans-unit.source: Whose Islam is the best (Who is the best Muslim)?
trans-unit.target: የማን እስልምና (ማን የተሻለ ሙስሊም ነው) የተሻለ ነው?

trans-unit.source: To feed (others) is a part of Islam.
To like for one's (Muslim's) brother what one likes for himself is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሰው (ሙስሊም የአምላክን) ወንድሙ እንደ ምን አንድ ሰው ለራሱ የተወደዱ እምነት አካል ነው.

trans-unit.source: To love the Messenger (Muhammad) (SAWS) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: መልክተኛውም (መሐመድ) እና በሽረት አባባል () ፍቅር, አንድ የእምነት ክፍል ነው.

trans-unit.source: Virtues of the Night of Qadr
Retiring to a Mosque for Remembrance of Allah (I'tikaf)
trans-unit.target: አላህ ለመታሰቢያዬ አንድ መስጊድ (I'tikaf) ወደ ጡረታ

trans-unit.source: Sales in which a Price is paid for Goods to be Delivered Later (As-Salam)
trans-unit.target: አንድ ዋጋ ዕቃዎች ይከፈላል ውስጥ የሽያጭ ከጊዜ በኋላ የደረሱ ዘንድ (እንደ-ራባይን)

trans-unit.source: Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሰው ሌላው (Al-Hawaala) አንድ ዕዳ ውስጥ Transferance

trans-unit.source: The Prophet (SAWS) used to take care of the people in preaching by selecting a suitable time so that they might not run away (or get bored).
trans-unit.target: እነሱ መሸሽ (ወይም አሰልቺ) እንጂ ዘንድ ስለዚህ ተስማሚ የሆነ ጊዜ በመምረጥ የስብከት ውስጥ ያሉ ሰዎችን ለመንከባከብ ጥቅም ላይ ነቢዩ (በሽረት).

trans-unit.source: Whoever fixed a special day for giving (a religious talk) to the students.
trans-unit.target: ማንም ተማሪዎች (አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ንግግር) በመስጠት ልዩ ቀን አስተካክለናል.

trans-unit.source: If Allah (azza wa jal) wants to do good to a person, He makes him comprehend the religion. [The understanding of the Qur'an and the Sunna (legal ways) of Prophet Muhammad (SAWS)].
trans-unit.target: አላህ (azza ወ jal) አንድ ሰው መልካም ማድረግ የሚፈልግ ከሆነ, እርሱ ወደ እርሱ ሃይማኖት መረዳት ያደርገዋል.

trans-unit.source: Wish to be like the one who has knowledge and Al-Hikmah (wisdom) [i.e. the knowledge of the Qur'an and the Sunna (legal ways) of the Prophet (SAWS)]. And 'Umar (RA) said: Everyone must acquire sound religious knowledge early before he becomes a chief. (Abu 'Abdullah said: The companions of the Prophet had studied inspite of the fact that they were old in age).
trans-unit.target: እውቀት እና አል-Hikmah (ጥበብ) [ያለው ዓይነት ሰው መሆን እፈልጋለሁ ማለትም

trans-unit.source: What has been said about the journey of Prophet Musa ('alaihi as-salam) (when he went) in the sea to meet Al-Khidr.
trans-unit.target: ነቢዩ ሙሳ ጉዞ በተመለከተ እንዲህ ተደርጓል ምንድን ነው ( 'alaihi እንደ-salam) (ሄደ ጊዜ) አል-Khidr ለማግኘት ወደ ባሕር ውስጥ.

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'O Allah! Bestow on hlm (Ibn 'Abbas) the knowledge of the Book (the Qur'an).'
At what age may youth be listened to (i.e. the quotation of the Hadith from a boy be acceptable).
trans-unit.target: ምን ዓመቱ ወጣት በመስማት ሊሆን ይችላል (ማለትም አንድ ልጅ ከ በሐዲት ላይ ጥቅስ ተቀባይነት).

trans-unit.source: To go out in search of knowledge.
Whoever is asked about knowledge while he is busy in some conversation, so he finished talking and then answered the questioner.
trans-unit.target: ከጥቂት ውይይት ውስጥ ስራ ላይ ነው ሳለ ማንም እውቀት ስለ ጠየቁት ነው, ስለዚህ እርሱ ተናግረው ሲጨርሱ; ከዚያም ጠያቂው መልሶ.

trans-unit.source: The superiority of a person who learns (Islam, becomes a religions scholar) and then teaches it to others.
trans-unit.target: የሚማር አንድ ሰው ያለውን የበላይነት (ኢስላም, አንድ ሃይማኖቶች ምሁር ይሆናል) ከዚያም ለሌሎች ያስተምራል.

trans-unit.source: (What is said regarding) the disappearance of the (religious) knowledge and the appearance of (religious) ignorance.
trans-unit.target: የ (ሃይማኖታዊ) እውቀት እንዲጠፉ እና (ሃይማኖታዊ) ባለማወቅ መልክ (እንዲህ ነው ምን በተመለከተ).

trans-unit.source: To give a religious verdict while riding an animal or standing on anything else.
trans-unit.target: አንድ እንስሳ በሚጓዙበት ወቅት ወይም ወደ ሌላ ማንኛውም ነገር ላይ ቆሞ ሳለ አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ብይን ለመስጠት.

trans-unit.source: Whoever gave a religious verdict by beckoning or by nodding.
trans-unit.target: ማንም ጠቅሶ ወይም እንደምትፀዳዳ አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ብይን ሰጠ.

trans-unit.source: The Prophet (saws) urged the people (mission) of 'Abdul Qais to memorize the faith and the (religious) knowledge (as he explained to them) and to inform (convey) to their people whom they left behind (at home).
trans-unit.target: ነብዩ (መጋዞች) (እርሱም እንደገለጸው) እምነት እና (ሃይማኖታዊ) እውቀት ለማስታወስ እና (ቤት) ወደ ኋላ የቀሩት ለማን ያላቸውን ሰዎች (ለማስተላለፍ) ለማሳወቅ በአብዱል Qais 'ሰዎች (ተልዕኮ) አሳስቧል.

trans-unit.source: To travel seeking an answer to a problematic matter, and to teach it to one's family.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ችግር ጉዳይ መልስ ይፈልጉ መጓዝ, እና አንድ ቤተሰብ ጋር ለማስተማር.

trans-unit.source: To fix the duties in rotation for learning (religious) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: Fi ጋር ?? (ሃይማኖታዊ) እውቀት ለመማር ሽክርክር ውስጥ ተግባራት x.

trans-unit.source: To be furious while preaching or teaching if one sees what one hates.
trans-unit.target: የስብከት ወይም አንድ በአንድ የሚጠላ ያያል ከሆነ እያስተማረ ሳለ ኃይለኛ መሆን.

trans-unit.source: Whoever knelt down before the Imam or a (religious) preacher.
trans-unit.target: ማንም ኢማሙ ወይም (ሃይማኖታዊ) ሰባኪ ፊት ተንበርክኮ.

trans-unit.source: Whoever raises his voice in (conveying) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: ማንም ሰው (ለማስተላለፍ) እውቀት ውስጥ ድምፁን ከፍ አድርጎ ያሰማል.

trans-unit.source: Repeating one's talk thrice in order to make others understand.
trans-unit.target: ትዕዛዝ ውስጥ ሦስት ጊዜ አንድ ሰው ንግግር ከመድገም ሌሎችን ለመረዳት ለማድረግ.

trans-unit.source: A man teaching (religion to) his woman-slave and his family.
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሰው ሲያስተምር (ሃይማኖት) ኢየሱስ ሴት-ባሪያ ቤተሰቡ.

trans-unit.source: The preaching (and teaching) of the (religious) knowledge to women by the Imam (chief):
How the (religious) knowledge will he taken away?
trans-unit.target: የ (ሃይማኖታዊ) ዕውቀት እርሱ እንዴት ይወሰድበታል ነው?

trans-unit.source: Should a day be fixed for women in order to teach them religion (apart from men)?
trans-unit.target: አንድ ቀን (ያለ ከሰው) ለእነሱ ሃይማኖት ለማስተማር ሲሉ ሴቶች መስተካከል አለበት?

trans-unit.source: Whoever heard something (but did not understand it) and then asked again till he understood it completely.
trans-unit.target: ሁሉ ነገር በሰማ (ግን አላስተዋሉም); ከዚያም ሙሉ በሙሉ መረዳት ድረስ እንደ ገና ጠየቁት.

trans-unit.source: It is incumbent on those who are present [in a religious meeting (or conference)] to convey the knowledge to those who are absent. (This statement has come from the Prophet (SAWS) upon the authority of Ibn 'Abbas).
trans-unit.target: ይህ ብርቅ የሆኑ ሰዎች እውቀት ለማስተላለፍ [አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ስብሰባ (ወይም ጉባኤ) ውስጥ] ያላችሁ ሰዎች ላይ ምእመኖቹንም ነው.

trans-unit.source: The sin of a person who tells a lie against the Prophet (SAWS).
trans-unit.target: ነቢዩ (በሽረት) ላይ ውሸትን ይነግረናል አንድ ሰው ወደ ኃጢአት ነው እንጂ.

trans-unit.source: Concerning the variety of words used by narrators conveying different significations regarding the concept of narrating and which has importance for the Hadith scholars only.
trans-unit.target: በሊቃውንት እና ይህም ብቻ ሐዲት ምሁራን ከፍተኛ ጠቀሜታ አለው ጽንሰ-ሐሳብ በተመለከተ የተለያዩ significations ለማስተላለፍ የትረካ ጥቅም ላይ ቃላት የተለያዩ በተመለከተ.

trans-unit.source: The knowledge and its teaching and preaching at night.
trans-unit.target: እውቀት እና ትምህርት ሌሊት ላይ መስበክ ነው.

trans-unit.source: To speak about (religious) knowledge at night.
(What is said regarding) the memorization of the (religious) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: የ (ሃይማኖታዊ) እውቀት ማጥናት (እንዲህ ነው ምን በተመለከተ).

trans-unit.source: To be quiet (and listen) to religious learned men.
trans-unit.target: ሃይማኖታዊ የተማሩ ሰዎች ዝም (እና ለማዳመጥ) ነው.

trans-unit.source: When a religious learned man is asked. "Who is the most learned person." (It is better for him to attribute or entrust absolute knowledge to Allah (azza wa jal), and to say, "Allah is the Most Learned (than anybody else).")
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ የተማረ ሰው ጠየቀው ጊዜ.

trans-unit.source: Whosoever, while standing, asked a religious learned man who was sitting (on a pulpit or a similar thing, about something).
trans-unit.target: ቆሞ ሳለ የሚያደርግ ሁሉ: (ነገር ስለ መረባርብ ወይም ተመሳሳይ ነገር ላይ,) ተቀምጦ ነበር; አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ የተማረ ሰው ጠየቀው.

trans-unit.source: To ask about a religious matter and to give a religious verdict (at Mina during Hajj) while doing the Rami of Jimar (throwing of pebbles at the Jimar in Mina during Hajj).
trans-unit.target: አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ጉዳይ በተመለከተ መጠየቅ እና Jimar ላይ Rami (በሐጅ ጊዜ: ምናንህ ውስጥ Jimar ላይ ጠጠር መወርወር) በማድረግ ላይ ሳለ (የሐጅ ወቅት: ምናንህ ላይ) አንድ ሃይማኖታዊ ብይን ለመስጠት.

trans-unit.source: The Statement of Allah (azza wa jal): "And of knowledge you (mankind) have been given only a little." (V. l7:85).
trans-unit.target: አላህ (azza ወ jal) ያለው መግለጫ: "እናም እውቀት (የሰው ልጆች) ብቻ ጥቂት ተሰጥቶኛል."

trans-unit.source: Whosoever left some optional things simply for the fear that some people may not be able to understand them and may fall into something more difficult.
trans-unit.target: ለሚወጣ ሁሉ በቀላሉ አንዳንድ ሰዎች እነሱን መረዳት አይችሉም ይችላል እና ይበልጥ አስቸጋሪ ነገር እንዳይወድቅ ከመፍራት የተነሣ አንዳንድ አማራጭ ሁሉን ትተን.

trans-unit.source: I Have Put Trust In Allah

In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful! Allah is the greatest, Allah is the greatest, Allah is the greatest, how perfect He is, The One Who has placed this (transport) at our service, and we ourselves would not have been capable of that, and of our Lord is our final destiny. O Allah we ask You for birr and taqwaa(comprehensive terms referring to all good actions and obedience) in this journey of ours, and we ask you for deeds which please You. O Allah, facilitate our journey and let us cover it's distance quickly. O Allah, You are the Companion on the journey and The Successor over the family, O Allah, I take refuge with you from the difficulties of travel, from having a change of hearts and being in a bad predicament, and I take refuge in You from an ill fated out come with wealth and family.

trans-unit.source: We have ended a new day and with it all dominion is Allah's. Praise is to Allah. None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, Who has no partner. To Allah belongs the dominion, and to Him is the praise and He is Able to do all things. My Lord, I ask You for the good things of this night and of the nights that come after it, and I seek refuge in You from the evil of this night and of the nights that come after it. My lord, I seek refuge in You from laziness and helpless old age. My Lord, I seek refuge in You from the punishment of Hell-fire, and from the punishment of the grave.
trans-unit.target: እኛ አዲስ ቀን አልቋል, እና ከእርሱ ጋር ሁሉ ኃይልንም የአላህ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, You bring us the end of the day as You bring us its beginning, You bring us life and You bring us death, and to You is our fate.
trans-unit.target: በእኛ በውስጡ መጀመሪያ ለማምጣት እንደ ሆይ! አላህ ለእኛ ቀን መጨረሻ ለማምጣት, አንተ ሕይወት የሚያመጣ እንዲሁም ለእኛ ሞትን ያመጣል, እና አንተ የእኛ ዕጣ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, I have ended another day and call upon You and upon the bearers of Your Throne, upon Your angels and all creation to bear witness that surely You are Allah, there is none worthy of worship but You alone, You have no partners, and that Muhammad is Your slave and Your messenger. (Recite four times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: ሆይ አላህ: እኔ ስለ ሌላ ቀን አልቋል እና የእርስዎ መላእክት በእርግጥ አንተ አላህ እንደሆነ ይመሰክር ዘንድ ፍጥረት ሁሉ ላይ: አንተ ላይ እና የእርስዎ ዐርሽ ተሸካሚዎች ላይ ይደውሉ አምልኮ የሚገባው ማንም የለም ነገር ግን ብቻ እናንተ ምንም አጋሮች አሉን,

trans-unit.source: O Allah, as I enter this evening whatever blessing has been received by me or anyone of Your creation is from You alone, You have no partner. All praise is for You and thanks is to You.
trans-unit.target: እኔ በእኔ የተቀበለው ወይም የእርስዎ ፍጥረት ማንኛውም ሰው ብቻ ከ ነው ተደርጓል ሁሉ በረከት በዚህ ምሽት ያስገቡ እንደ ሆይ! አላህ አንተ ምንም አጋር የላቸውም.

trans-unit.source: We have ended a new day and with it all the dominion which belongs to Allah, Lord of all that exists. O Allah, I ask You for the good things of this night, its victory, its help, its light, its blessings, and its guidance. I seek refuge in You from the evil that is in it and from the evil that follows it.
trans-unit.target: እኛ አዲስ ቀን እና ከእርሱ ጋር መኖሩን አላህ የሁሉ ጌታ ለአላህ ሁሉ ክብርና አብቅቶለታል.

trans-unit.source: We end this day upon the natural religion of Islam, the word of sincere devotion, the religion of our Prophet Muhammad (peace and blessings of Allah be upon him), and the faith of our father Ibrahim. He was upright (in worshipping Allah), and a Muslim. He was not of those who worship others besides Allah.
trans-unit.target: እኛም እስልምና, ቅን ያደሩ ቃል, የእኛ ነቢዩ መሐመድ (የአላህ ሰላምና በረከት በእርሱ ላይ ይሁን) ሃይማኖት የተፈጥሮ ሃይማኖት ላይ ዛሬ, እና ከአባታችን ኢብራሂም እምነት ያበቃል.

trans-unit.source: I seek refuge in the Perfect Words of Allah from the evil of what He has created. (Recite three times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: እኔ ከፈጠረው ነገር ከክፉ በአላህ ፍጹም ቃላት ውስጥ እጠበቃለሁ.

trans-unit.source: We have risen this evening and sovereignty is all Allah’s. Praise is due to Allah alone, He has no partner, there is no God but Him, unto whom is our fate.
trans-unit.target: በዚህ ምሽት ተነሥቶአል እና ሉዓላዊነት ሁሉ የአላህ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah! I rise up in the evening with the blessing, strength, and protection, all of which you have bestowed upon me. Complete your blessing, the strength (you bestowed upon me) and your protection, in this life and the hereafter.

We have entered a new day and with it all dominion is Allah's. Praise is to Allah. None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, Who has no partner. To Allah belongs the dominion, and to Him is the praise and He is Able to do all things. My Lord, I ask You for the goodness of this day and of the days that come after it, and I seek refuge in You from the evil of this day and of the days that come after it. My lord, I seek refuge in You from laziness and helpless old age. My Lord, I seek refuge in You from the punishment of Hell-fire, and from the punishment of the grave.
trans-unit.target: እኛ አዲስ ቀን አስገብተዋል ከዚህ ጋር ሁሉ ኃይልንም የአላህ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, by You we enter the morning and by You we enter the evening, by You we live and by You we die, and to You is the Final Return.
trans-unit.target: የኾንክ አላህ አንተ እኛ ማለዳ ያስገቡ እና አንተ እኛ በሕይወት በ አንተ እኛ, ምሽት ያስገቡ እና አንተ እኛ መሞት, አንተ ወደ የመጨረሻ ተመለስ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, I have entered a new morning and call upon You and upon the bearers of Your Throne, upon Your angels and all creation to bear witness that surely You are Allah, there is none worthy of worship but You alone, You have no partners, and that Muhammad is Your slave and Your messenger. (Recite four times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: አላህ ሆይ, እኔ አዲስ ጠዋት አስገብተዋል እና የእርስዎ መላእክት በእርግጥ አንተ አላህ እንደሆነ ይመሰክር ዘንድ ፍጥረት ሁሉ ላይ: አንተ ላይ እና የእርስዎ ዐርሽ ተሸካሚዎች ላይ ይደውሉ አምልኮ የሚገባው ማንም የለም ነገር ግን ብቻ እናንተ ምንም አጋሮች አሉን

trans-unit.source: O Allah, as I enter this morning whatever blessing has been received by me or anyone of Your creation is from You alone, You have no partner. All praise is for You and thanks is to You.
trans-unit.target: እኔ በእኔ የተቀበለው ወይም የእርስዎ ፍጥረት ማንኛውም ሰው ብቻ ከ ነው ተደርጓል ሁሉ በረከት በዚህ ጠዋት ያስገቡ እንደ ሆይ! አላህ አንተ ምንም አጋር የላቸውም.

trans-unit.source: We have entered a new day and with it all the dominion which belongs to Allah, Lord of all that exists. O Allah, I ask You for the goodness of this day, its victory, its help, its light, its blessings, and its guidance. I seek refuge in You from the evil that is in it and from the evil that follows it.
trans-unit.target: እኛ አዲስ ቀን እና ከእርሱ ጋር መኖሩን አላህ የሁሉ ጌታ ለአላህ ሁሉ ክብርና አስገብተዋል.

trans-unit.source: We have entered a new day upon the natural religion of Islam, the word of sincere devotion, the religion of our Prophet Muhammad (peace and blessings of Allah be upon him), and the faith of our father Ibrahim. He was upright (in worshipping Allah), and a Muslim. He was not of those who worship others besides Allah.
trans-unit.target: እኛም እስልምና, ቅን ያደሩ ቃል, የእኛ ነቢዩ መሐመድ (የአላህ ሰላምና በረከት በእርሱ ላይ ይሁን) ሃይማኖት ተፈጥሯዊ ሃይማኖት, እና ከአባታችን ኢብራሂም እምነት ላይ አዲስ ቀን አስገብተዋል.

trans-unit.source: Glory is to Allah and praise is to Him, by the multitude of His creation, by His Pleasure, by the weight of His Throne, and by the extent of His Words. (Recite three times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: ክብር ወደ አላህ ብቻ ነው እና ምስጋና የእርሱ ዐርሽ በሚዛን: የእርሱ ተድላን በማድረግ, የእርሱ ፍጥረት ሕዝብም ወደ እርሱ ነው; የእርሱ ቃላት ምን ያህል ነው.

trans-unit.source: We have risen this morning and sovereignty is all Allah’s. Praise is due to Allah alone, He has no partner, there is no God but Him, unto whom is the return.
trans-unit.target: እኛ በዚህ ጠዋት ተነሥቶአል እና ሉዓላዊነት ሁሉ የአላህ ነው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah! I rise up in the morning with the blessing, strength, and protection, all of which you have bestowed upon me. Complete your blessing, the strength (you bestowed upon me) and your protection, in this life and the hereafter.

O Allah, You are my Lord, there is none worthy of worship but You. You created me and I am your slave. I keep Your covenant, and my pledge to You so far as I am able, I seek refuge in You from the evil of what I have done, I admit to Your blessings upon me, and I admit to my misdeeds. Forgive me, for there is none who may forgive sins but You.
trans-unit.target: የኾንክ አላህ አንተ አምልኮ ነገር ግን አንተ የሚገባ ማንም የለም, ጌታ ሆይ ናቸው.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, make me healthy in my body. O Allah, preserve for me my hearing. O Allah, preserve for me my sight. There is none worthy of worship but You. O Allah, I seek refuge in You from disbelief and poverty and I seek refuge in You from the punishment of the grave. There is none worthy of worship but You. (Recite three times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: የኾንክ አላህ በሰውነቴ ውስጥ እኔን ጤናማ ማድረግ.

In the Name of Allah, Who with His Name nothing can cause harm in the earth nor in the heavens, and He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing. (Recite three times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: በአላህ ስም የእርሱ ስም ምንም ጋር ማን ወደ ምድር ላይ ቢሆን ወይም በሰማያት ውስጥ ጉዳት, እና እርሱ ሁሉ-ሰሚው ዐዋቂ ነው ይችላሉ.

In The Name Of Allah Most Beneficent Most Merciful
trans-unit.target: አላህ በጣም ጠቃሚ በጣም አዛኝ ስም

trans-unit.source: We ask you O that He is Allah who there is no God except He
trans-unit.target: እርሱ በቀር ምንም አምላክ የለም አላህ ነው ሆይ! እኛ መጠየቅ

trans-unit.source: Verily all praise is for Allah, we praise Him, seek His help and guidance and His forgiveness; and we seek refuge in Allah from the evil of ourselves and from the sinfulness of our actions. Whosoever Allah guides, then none can misguide him, and whosoever Allah misguides, there can be no guide for him. I testify there is no deity worthy of worship except Allah alone, and I testify that Muhammad is His servant and messenger.
trans-unit.target: እውነት ሁሉ ምስጋና እኛም የእርሱን እርዳታ እና መመሪያ እና ይቅርታ ፈልጉ እርሱን አመስግኑት; አላህ ነው;

trans-unit.source: To proceed: Certainly the best speech is the Book of Allah and the finest guidance is the guidance of Muhammad, the prayers of Allah upon him and peace. The most evil affair is a newly invented matter in religion and every newly invented matter is innovation and every innovation is straying and every straying is in the fire.
trans-unit.target: መቀጠል: በእርግጥ ምርጥ ንግግር የአላህ መጽሐፍ ነው; ከምርጥ መመሪያ መሐመድ መመሪያ, በእርሱ ሰላም ላይ የአላህ ጸሎት ነው.

Praise is to Allah Who gives us life after He has caused us to die and to Him is the return.

trans-unit.source: There is none worthy of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner. His is the dominion and to Him belongs all praise, and He is Able to do all things. Glory is to Allah. Praise is to Allah. There is none worthy of worship but Allah. Allah is the Most Great. There is no might and no power except by Allah's leave, the Exalted, the Mighty. My Lord, forgive me.
trans-unit.target: ምንም አጋር ያለው አምልኮ የሚገባው ግን ብቻውን አላህ ማንም የለም.

trans-unit.source: Praise is to Allah Who gave strength to my body and returned my soul to me and permitted me to remember Him.
trans-unit.target: ምስጋና ሰውነቴ ብርታት ሰጠኝ ወደ እኔ ነፍሴ ተመልሶ እርሱን ለማስታወስ ፈቀደልኝ ማን ወደ አላህ ብቻ ነው.

trans-unit.source: Praise is to Allah Who has clothed me with this (garment) (3x) and provided it for me, though I was powerless myself and incapable.
trans-unit.target: ምስጋና ይህ (ልብስ) ጋር ወደ እኔ መጥታችኋልና ማን ነው አላህ (3x) ነው; እኔም ራሴ አቅመ እና መቀበሉ ነበር ቢሆንም, ለእኔ ያቀረቡት.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, praise is to You. You have clothed me. I ask You for its goodness and the goodness of what it has been made for, and I seek Your protection from the evil of it and the evil of what it has been made for.
Glory to my Lord the Exalted (3x).
Glory is to You, O Allah, our Lord, and praise is Yours. O Allah, forgive me.
